  hospital_course: `ms. ___ with admitted with erythema from her right breast. she was ultimately started on IV abx and taken to ___ for drainage, where 35 cc of pus were removed. the following day she was taken to OR for removal of implant on . a vac was placed and she was continued on abx. on POD2, she was taken back again for another vac change and washout. pus was found the first trip to OR but everything looked clean on the 2dnd OR trip. another vac was placed and she was sent home on Bactrim. she had remained afebrile and felt well after the washouts. she tolerated a regular diet and ambulated independently. no nausea or vomiting, and she was put on a home vac. plan to follow up a couple of days after washout for another debridement and eval.`,
